sql:
SELECT stop_id 
FROM stops
WHERE is_green_line = 1;

SELECT stop_name, direction_id
FROM stops
WHERE platform_number > 10;

external_knowledge:
- In this context, "beacons" refers to stops; 
- "light the path of the Green Line" metaphorically means serving the Green Line; 
- "passengers can embark or disembark" refers to the function of stops.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM stops
WHERE is_green_line = 1;

SELECT stop_name, direction_id
FROM stops
ORDER BY platform_number ASC;

SELECT stops.stop_name, stations.station_name 
FROM stops 
INNER JOIN stations ON stops.station_id = stations.station_id;

SELECT station_id, station_name, capacity
FROM stations
WHERE capacity = (SELECT MAX(capacity) FROM stations);

SELECT AVG(total_stops) AS average_stops_per_route
FROM (
  SELECT route_id, COUNT(*) AS total_stops
  FROM schedules
  GROUP BY route_id
);

external_knowledge:
- Red Line: A significant transit line in the city's transportation network; 
- Latitude 40: Represents a geographical line indicating a specific altitude above the equator;
- New Year's Day 2022: January 1, 2022, marking the start of a new year.

